When function call is done within a function then you can write it as @Bravo has suggested:

```javascript
let result = await fooClass.fooFunc();
```

Link for [async/await] [1]

  [1]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/JavaScript/Asynchronous/Async_await

If you are calling it outside a function then :

```
(async function(){
   let result = await fooClass.fooFunc();
})();
```

